      <description>&lt;img src=&#34;../../../images/ctf/gitbad/image.png&#34; alt=&#34;logo&#34; style=&#34;display: block; margin: 0 auto;&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GitBad&lt;/strong&gt; was one of those challenges that felt a bit tricky at first, but ended up being a lot of fun to dig into. We were given the source code of a web application and a running instance to interact with. The app allowed users to register and upload a ZIP file that contained a .git folder—essentially simulating a Git project upload.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sign up Page:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
